<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-20T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-20T07:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/628</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-20T13:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.42 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2873. I have this morning presented to the Minister for Foreign
                                Affairs a note according to the instructions contained in your 1077,
                                September 5, 3 p.m., and 1122, September 13, 8 p.m. Before doing so
                                I consulted my colleagues who all advised me to wait no longer as
                                they feared there would be great delay before all our different
                                instructions could be brought into conformity.</p>
                            <pb facs="0457" n="1291" xml:id="pg_1291"/>
                            <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs said he would send me the statistics
                                asked for as soon as possible, but that he would be unable to comply
                                with the request for the text of any agreement with Germany. I do
                                not think this last point need be pressed as the Minister for
                                Foreign Affairs gave me clearly to understand that the coal
                                agreement which expires September 30 was the only one still binding.
                                Stockholm to London.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>